# Abstract

This document specifies the canonical binary serialization format for Kapnet
objects. It defines field ordering, scalar encodings, length prefixes, object
tags, extension sections, and rejection rules for non-canonical encodings.
Canonical serialization is required for deterministic hashing, signing,
replay, proof validation, and interoperability across implementations.

